## Context

Live `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris` takes ~2–4 minutes
on the 223-record corpus, and re-runs (which are common when iterating on
gap rules or thresholds) pay the full network cost every time.

ARCHITECTURE.md §2.3 anticipates this:
> Add HTTP response cache only when a run takes more than ~30 seconds
> end-to-end on `ArchiveCCS.ris`.

That threshold has been crossed. The cache must be safe to `rm -rf`
without breaking correctness — re-running with the cache wiped must
produce the same fixed RIS as a fresh run.

## Actions

1. Add `hishel>=0.0.30` to `pyproject.toml` runtime deps. (HTTP-spec-
   compliant cache for httpx; respects upstream `Cache-Control` headers
   and ETags. MIT-licensed, CeCILL-B compatible.)
2. In `src/maiba/resolvers/openalex.py` and `crossref.py`, replace
   `httpx.Client(...)` construction with a `hishel.CacheClient(...)`
   wrapping the same transport, configured with a filesystem storage
   backend at a path derived from `Config`.
3. Extend `config/maiba.yaml` `http` section:
   ```yaml
   http:
     timeout_s: 10
     ...
     cache_dir: ~/.cache/maiba/http     # safe to rm -rf
     cache_ttl_s: 2592000               # 30 days; resolver responses are stable
   ```
4. Extend `Config.HttpConfig` model in `src/maiba/config.py` with
   `cache_dir: str` and `cache_ttl_s: int`.
5. Expand `~` and create the cache dir on first use (do not fail if it
   already exists).
6. Add `--no-cache` to `maiba scan`. When set, instantiate resolvers
   with caching disabled (still uses httpx, just no hishel wrapper).
7. Add `maiba clear-cache` verb that removes `cache_dir`. Convenience
   only; `rm -rf <cache_dir>` is equivalent.
8. Append §9 entry to ARCHITECTURE.md:
   `2026-04-28 — HTTP cache → DECIDED: hishel (filesystem, deletable).`
   This formally relaxes the §2.3 "zero state" decision per the
   "if runtime grows past ~30 s" escape hatch already documented there.

## Test (TDD red step)

```python
# tests/test_cache.py
from pathlib import Path

import respx
from httpx import Response

from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.model import Item
from maiba.resolvers.openalex import OpenAlexResolver


@respx.mock
def test_resolver_uses_cache_on_second_call(tmp_path):
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    cfg.http.cache_dir = str(tmp_path / "cache")

    route = respx.get(url__regex=r".*api\.openalex\.org/works/doi:.*").mock(
        return_value=Response(
            200,
            headers={"cache-control": "max-age=86400"},
            json={
                "title": "X",
                "publication_year": 2020,
                "authorships": [],
                "doi": "https://doi.org/10.1/x",
            },
        )
    )
    resolver = OpenAlexResolver(cfg)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="X", DO="10.1/x")

    resolver.resolve(item)
    resolver.resolve(item)

    assert route.call_count == 1, "second call should be served from cache"


@respx.mock
def test_no_cache_flag_bypasses_cache(tmp_path):
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    cfg.http.cache_dir = str(tmp_path / "cache")

    route = respx.get(url__regex=r".*api\.openalex\.org/works/doi:.*").mock(
        return_value=Response(200, json={"title": "X", "publication_year": 2020,
                                          "authorships": [], "doi": "https://doi.org/10.1/x"})
    )
    # Construct resolver in no-cache mode (API TBD — likely a kwarg on __init__).
    resolver = OpenAlexResolver(cfg, use_cache=False)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="X", DO="10.1/x")

    resolver.resolve(item)
    resolver.resolve(item)

    assert route.call_count == 2, "no-cache mode should hit the network every time"
```

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green; both cache tests pass.
- `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris` (live, dry-run)
  populates `~/.cache/maiba/http`. A second invocation is at least
  5× faster.
- `rm -rf ~/.cache/maiba/http` between runs restores full network
  behavior without breaking correctness.
- `--no-cache` flag bypasses the cache.
- `maiba clear-cache` removes `cache_dir`.
- ARCHITECTURE.md §9 entry added.
- `make lint` green.
